SIDIS event generator

1. get lhapdf and compile
mkdir lhapdf
wget http://www.hepforge.org/archive/lhapdf/lhapdf-5.8.5.tar.gz
tar zxf lhapdf-5.8.5.tar.gz
cd lhapdf-5.8.5
./configure --prefix=/PathOflhapdf CC=/usr/bin/gcc CXX=/usr/bin/g++ FC=/usr/bin/gfortran
make
make install
cd ../share/lhapdf
wget http://www.hepforge.org/archive/lhapdf/pdfsets/5.8.5/cteq6m.LHpdf

2. compile and run
cd collider
setenv ROOTSYS /apps/root/5.28-00c-64bit
setenv PATH ${ROOTSYS}/bin:${PATH}
setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH ${ROOTSYS}/lib
#setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH ${ROOTSYS}/lib:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}
setenv LHAPDF /PathOflhapdf
setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH ${LHAPDF}/lib:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}
make

3. running the code
setup the same env 
run "./collider" to see all running options

4. analysis result
also copy acceptance rootfile into analysis directory

generate weight with correct normlization
root[] .x generate_weight.C("rootfile");

root[] .x generate_plot.C("pion",1,0)
flag is explained in the code.


================ from Min Huang ============

In general, use perl scripts to run the code or generate file list 

Makefile: $ make O=(C code name without '.C')
eg, skim.C, you make it as make O=skim



/simulation
    collider_new.C  // generate simulation events, with all the kinematic variables, cross section info
    

/projection/skim
    skim.C  // cut each data file from /simulation to pieces in each z, pt bins

/projection
    makebin.C // use rootfiles in each z,pt bin to make Q2, x bins. Apply cross section in this step, and try to have almost same number of events in each bin, the number of events is decided by the uncertainty we want to achieve. 
   This code will generate files in /out_rootfiles_p/m, and database_p/m

   get_results.C // get the average value of kinematic variables and uncertainty of angular asymmetry info of each bin. 
   Generate files in /results

 /plot
   make plots.
